{"title_page": "Bollywood Diaries", "text_new": "{{in use}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Bollywood Diaries\n| image = BollywoodDiaries Poster.jpg\n| caption = Official poster\n| director = [[K.D.Satyam]]\n| producer = Dr. Sattar Diwan\n| writer = [[K.D.Satyam]]\n| starring = [[Raima Sen]][[Salim Diwan]], [[Ashish Vidyarthi]]\n| music = [[Vipin Patwa]]\n| cinematography = [[Dev Agarwal]]\n| studio =Rehab Pictures Pvt Ltd\n| distributor = [[Zee Entertainment Enterprises#Movie productions|Zee Studios]]\n| released = {{Film date|df=y|2016|02|26}}\n| runtime = 125 minutes\n| country = India\n| language = [[Hindi]]\n}}\n'''''Bollywood Diaries''''' is a 2016 Indian Hindi-language [[drama film]] written and directed by [[K.D.Satyam]]. It features [[Raima Sen]], [[Salim Diwan]], and [[Ashish Vidyarthi]] in lead roles, along with Karuna Pandey and [[Vineet Kumar Singh]].<ref>{{cite web|title = Raima Sen to play sex worker in Bollywood Diaries|url = http://www.thedailystar.net/raima-sen-to-play-sex-worker-in-bollywood-diaries-48409|website = The Daily Star|accessdate = 2015-11-27}}</ref> Produced by Dr. Sattar Diwan under the banner of Rehab Pictures Private Limited, the film was released worldwide on 26 February 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Film-industry-all-praise-for-Bollywood-Diaries/articleshow/51056342.cms|title=Film industry all praise for 'Bollywood Diaries' - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nThe story is about three unrelated individuals \u2013 Rohit (Salim Diwan), a guy working at a call-center in Delhi, Vishnu (Ashish Vidyarthi), a retired middle-aged government servant from Bhilai and Imli (Raima Sen), a prostitute from Sonagachi, Kolkata. All three of them aspire to become [[Bollywood]] actors and the story follows their struggle to make it big in Bollywood. The movie also shows the passion and madness of common individuals behind Bollywood. <ref>{{cite web|title = Raima Sen to play a Sonagachi sex worker in KD Satyam\u2019s Bollywood Diaries|url = http://www.india.com/showbiz/raima-sen-to-play-a-sonagachi-sex-worker-in-kd-satyams-bollywood-diaries-185111/|website = India.com|date = 2014-11-02|accessdate = 2015-12-07}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Raima Sen]] as Imli\n* [[Salim Diwan]] as Rohit\n* [[Ashish Vidyarthi]] as Vishnu\n* Karuna Pandey as Lata\n* [[Vineet Kumar Singh]] as Daman\n* Robin Das as Sundar Das\n* Ekavali Khanna as Raveena\n\n== Production ==\n\n[[Principal photography]] of the film began in October 2014 and the shooting started the month after that.<ref>{{Cite news|title = Raima Sen starts filming \u2018Bollywood Diaries\u2019|url = http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/raima-sen-starts-filming-bollywood-diaries/|work = The Indian Express|date = 2014-11-02|accessdate = 2015-11-27}}</ref> The film was shot in [[Bhilai]], [[Kolkata]] and [[Delhi]]. During the filming, Ashish Vidyarthi suffered a mishap when he nearly drowned in river [[Shivnath River|Shivnath]] before being rescued by a policeman.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Policeman rescues Ashish Vidyarthi from drowning on set|url = http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/celebrity/policeman-rescues-ashish-vidyarthi-from-drowning-on-set_1487898.html|publisher = Zee News|accessdate = 2015-11-26}}</ref>\n\nThe cinematography was by [[Dev Agarwal]], the editing crew was led by Praveen Angre. The dialogues was written by [[K.D.Satyam]] and Anand VRS Tomar. Dr. Sagar wrote the lyrics for all the songs in the film. The songs were composed by [[Vipin Patwa]], while the background score was done by Dev Guru. The crew also includes Shrjil Khan as Choreographer, Nilesh S. Gorkshe as Art Director, Tony Arora as Line Producer, Ajay Kumar P. B. as Sound Mixing Engineer, and Mayank Dixit as Casting director.\n\n== Release ==\nThe film was released on 26 February 2016 across India.\n\n== Critical response ==\n''[[The Deccan Chronicle]]'' described ''Bollywood Diaries'' as a brilliant tribute to the struggling actors of Bollywood.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|title = Bollywood Diaries movie review: Brilliant tribute to Bollywood struggling actors|url = http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/260216/bollywood-diaries-brilliant-tribute-to-bollywood-struggling-actors.html|website = Deccan Chronicle|access-date = 2016-02-26|language = en-GB}}</ref> Martin D'souza of ''Glamsham'' called it an honest film with a great connect.<ref>{{Cite web|title = BOLLYWOOD DIARIES Movie Review: BOLLYWOOD DIARIES is an honest film with a great connect|url = http://www.glamsham.com/movies/reviews/bollywood-diaries-movie-review.asp#|website = Glamsham|access-date = 2016-02-25|language = en-GB}}</ref> Bollywood Diaries has been critically acclaimed by many critics, Subhash K Jha \u2013 3.5 stars Must not miss this aspirational Bollywood saga<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://skjbollywoodnews.com/2016/02/bollywood-diaries-movie-review-must-not-miss-this-aspirational-bollywood-saga/4157868.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=29 February 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305054129/http://skjbollywoodnews.com/2016/02/bollywood-diaries-movie-review-must-not-miss-this-aspirational-bollywood-saga/4157868.html |archive-date=5 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Rahul desai A well-acted, unnerving film about Bollywood aspirations<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.catchnews.com/bollywood-news/bollywood-diaries-movie-review-raima-sen-film-is-a-well-acted-film-about-bollywood-aspirations-bollywood-films-2016-1456391287.html|title=Bollywood Diaries movie review: A well-acted, unnerving film about Bollywood aspirations|website=CatchNews.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>. Rohit Bhatnagar, Deccan Chronicle \u2013 3 Stars\nBrilliant tribute to Bollywood Struggling actors<ref name=\":0\" />. Martin D\u2019Souza, Glamsham.com \u2013 3 stars\nAn honest film with Great connect\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.glamsham.com/en/movie-review-bollywood-diaries|title=Bollywood Diaries Movie Review, Rating, Cast and Crew, Release Date|last=Glamsham|website=Glamsham|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\nJohnson Thomas, Free Press Journal \u2013 3 Stars, A bittersweet story that has passion and substance and is smartly devoid of formulaic expressionism. <ref>http://www.freepressjournal.in/movie-review-bollywood-diaries-a-requiem-for-dreams-unfulfilled/790929<nowiki/>{{Dead link|date={{subst:CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{subst:CURRENTYEAR}}}}</ref>\nBollyvision.com \u2013 3 Stars An Honest Film<ref>https://www.bollyvisionnews.com/bollywood-diaries-movie-review-it-is-an-honest-film-watch-here/{{Dead link|date=June 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}<nowiki/>{{Dead link|date={{subst:CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{subst:CURRENTYEAR}}}}</ref> Box Office India \u2013 Worth a dekho<ref>http://www.boxofficeindia.co.in/bollywood-diaries-2/<nowiki/>{{Dead link|date={{subst:CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{subst:CURRENTYEAR}}}}</ref> Satyam\u2019s strength as a storyteller comes to the fore since he delves well into the psyche of these diverse characters, without making it come across as overburdening or depressing. The cinematography by Dev Agarwal was brilliant as he is creates stark images, capturing the energy of the characters with an unforced realism. By Joginder Tuteja \u2013 3 Star<ref>http://www.moviereviewpreview.com/movie-review-bollywood-diaries-a-dramatic-affair-which-doesnt-get-overbearing/51998/<nowiki/>{{Dead link|date={{subst:CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{subst:CURRENTYEAR}}}}</ref> Subhash K JHA  great reviews <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/features/|title=Featured Movie News {{!}} Featured Bollywood News - Bollywood Hungama|last=Hungama|first=Bollywood|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>. An ordinary film that  touches the hear \u2013 3 star by Divay  Agarwal<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moviecrow.com/News/11325/bollywood-diaries-review---an-ordinary-film-that-touches-the-heart|title=Bollywood Diaries Review - An ordinary film that touches the heart!|website=www.moviecrow.com|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> Komal Nahta-  Bollywood Dairies is s very real portrayal of strugglers in Bollywood. It is a genuinely good attempt which should be seen by lovers of cinema and Bollywood.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.moviesportal.pk/bollywood-movies/|title=Bollywood Movies Cinema|date=2013-12-22|work=Movies Portal|access-date=2017-05-20|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|5216810}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:2016 films]]\n[[Category:Films about Bollywood]]\n", "text_old": "{{in use}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Bollywood Diaries\n| image = BollywoodDiaries Poster.jpg\n| caption = Official poster\n| director = [[K.D.Satyam]]\n| producer = Dr. Sattar Diwan\n| writer = [[K.D.Satyam]]\n| starring = [[Raima Sen]][[Salim Diwan]], [[Ashish Vidyarthi]]\n| music = [[Vipin Patwa]]\n| cinematography = [[Dev Agarwal]]\n| studio =Rehab Pictures Pvt Ltd\n| distributor = [[Zee Entertainment Enterprises#Movie productions|Zee Studios]]\n| released = {{Film date|df=y|2016|02|26}}\n| runtime = 125 minutes\n| country = India\n| language = [[Hindi]]\n}}\n'''''Bollywood Diaries''''' is a 2016 Indian Hindi-language [[drama film]] written and directed by [[K.D.Satyam]]. It features [[Raima Sen]], [[Salim Diwan]], and [[Ashish Vidyarthi]] in lead roles, along with Karuna Pandey and [[Vineet Kumar Singh]].<ref>{{cite web|title = Raima Sen to play sex worker in Bollywood Diaries|url = http://www.thedailystar.net/raima-sen-to-play-sex-worker-in-bollywood-diaries-48409|website = The Daily Star|accessdate = 2015-11-27}}</ref> Produced by Dr. Sattar Diwan under the banner of Rehab Pictures Private Limited, the film was released worldwide on 26 February 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Film-industry-all-praise-for-Bollywood-Diaries/articleshow/51056342.cms|title=Film industry all praise for 'Bollywood Diaries' - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nThe story is about three unrelated individuals \u2013 Rohit (Salim Diwan), a guy working at a call-center in Delhi, Vishnu (Ashish Vidyarthi), a retired middle-aged government servant from Bhilai and Imli (Raima Sen), a prostitute from Sonagachi, Kolkata. All three of them aspire to become [[Bollywood]] actors and the story follows their struggle to make it big in Bollywood. The movie also shows the passion and madness of common individuals behind Bollywood. <ref>{{cite web|title = Raima Sen to play a Sonagachi sex worker in KD Satyam\u2019s Bollywood Diaries|url = http://www.india.com/showbiz/raima-sen-to-play-a-sonagachi-sex-worker-in-kd-satyams-bollywood-diaries-185111/|website = India.com|date = 2014-11-02|accessdate = 2015-12-07}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Raima Sen]] as Imli\n* [[Salim Diwan]] as Rohit\n* [[Ashish Vidyarthi]] as Vishnu\n* Karuna Pandey as Lata\n* [[Vineet Kumar Singh]] as Daman\n* Robin Das as Sundar Das\n* Ekavali Khanna as Raveena\n\n== Production ==\n\n[[Principal photography]] of the film began in October 2014 and the shooting started the month after that.<ref>{{Cite news|title = Raima Sen starts filming \u2018Bollywood Diaries\u2019|url = http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/raima-sen-starts-filming-bollywood-diaries/|work = The Indian Express|date = 2014-11-02|accessdate = 2015-11-27}}</ref> The film was shot in [[Bhilai]], [[Kolkata]] and [[Delhi]]. During the filming, [[Ashish Vidyarthi]] suffered a mishap when he nearly drowned in river [[Shivnath River|Shivnath]] before being rescued by a policeman.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Policeman rescues Ashish Vidyarthi from drowning on set|url = http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/celebrity/policeman-rescues-ashish-vidyarthi-from-drowning-on-set_1487898.html|publisher = Zee News|accessdate = 2015-11-26}}</ref>\n\nThe cinematography was by [[Dev Agarwal]], the editing crew was led by Praveen Angre. The dialogues was written by [[K.D.Satyam]] and Anand VRS Tomar. Dr. Sagar wrote the lyrics for all the songs in the film. The songs were composed by [[Vipin Patwa]], while the background score was done by Dev Guru. The crew also includes Shrjil Khan as Choreographer, Nilesh S. Gorkshe as Art Director, Tony Arora as Line Producer, Ajay Kumar P. B. as Sound Mixing Engineer, and Mayank Dixit as Casting director.\n\n== Release ==\nThe film was released on 26 February 2016 across India.\n\n== Critical response ==\n''[[The Deccan Chronicle]]'' described ''Bollywood Diaries'' as a brilliant tribute to the struggling actors of Bollywood.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|title = Bollywood Diaries movie review: Brilliant tribute to Bollywood struggling actors|url = http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/260216/bollywood-diaries-brilliant-tribute-to-bollywood-struggling-actors.html|website = Deccan Chronicle|access-date = 2016-02-26|language = en-GB}}</ref> Martin D'souza of ''Glamsham'' called it an honest film with a great connect.<ref>{{Cite web|title = BOLLYWOOD DIARIES Movie Review: BOLLYWOOD DIARIES is an honest film with a great connect|url = http://www.glamsham.com/movies/reviews/bollywood-diaries-movie-review.asp#|website = Glamsham|access-date = 2016-02-25|language = en-GB}}</ref> Bollywood Diaries has been critically acclaimed by many critics, Subhash K Jha \u2013 3.5 stars Must not miss this aspirational Bollywood saga<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://skjbollywoodnews.com/2016/02/bollywood-diaries-movie-review-must-not-miss-this-aspirational-bollywood-saga/4157868.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=29 February 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305054129/http://skjbollywoodnews.com/2016/02/bollywood-diaries-movie-review-must-not-miss-this-aspirational-bollywood-saga/4157868.html |archive-date=5 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Rahul desai A well-acted, unnerving film about Bollywood aspirations<ref>http://www.catchnews.com/bollywood-news/bollywood-diaries-movie-review-raima-sen-film-is-a-well-acted-film-about-bollywood-aspirations-bollywood-films-2016-1456391287.html</ref>. Rohit Bhatnagar, Deccan Chronicle \u2013 3 Stars\nBrilliant tribute to Bollywood Struggling actors<ref name=\":0\" />. Martin D\u2019Souza, Glamsham.com \u2013 3 stars\nAn honest film with Great connect\n<ref>http://www.glamsham.com/movies/reviews/bollywood-diaries-movie-review.asp</ref>\nJohnson Thomas, Free Press Journal \u2013 3 Stars, A bittersweet story that has passion and substance and is smartly devoid of formulaic expressionism. <ref>http://www.freepressjournal.in/movie-review-bollywood-diaries-a-requiem-for-dreams-unfulfilled/790929 -</ref>\nBollyvision.com \u2013 3 Stars An Honest Film<ref>https://www.bollyvisionnews.com/bollywood-diaries-movie-review-it-is-an-honest-film-watch-here/{{Dead link|date=June 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Box Office India \u2013 Worth a dekho<ref>http://www.boxofficeindia.co.in/bollywood-diaries-2/</ref> Satyam\u2019s strength as a storyteller comes to the fore since he delves well into the psyche of these diverse characters, without making it come across as overburdening or depressing. The cinematography by [[Dev Agarwal]] was brilliant as he is creates stark images, capturing the energy of the characters with an unforced realism. By Joginder Tuteja \u2013 3 Star<ref>http://www.moviereviewpreview.com/movie-review-bollywood-diaries-a-dramatic-affair-which-doesnt-get-overbearing/51998/</ref> Subhash K JHA  great reviews <ref>http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/9815</ref>. An ordinary film that  touches the hear \u2013 3 star by Divay  Agarwal<re