ey's Crazy Car Caper\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|9|23}}\n| ShortSummary = When a new car is stolen, Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels investigate.\n| LineColor = 3abba7\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 20\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 4\n| Title = Cavey's Mexicali 500\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|9|30}}\n| ShortSummary = When four [[Aztec calendars]] are stolen, Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels decide to investigate.\n| LineColor = 3abba7\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 21\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 5\n| Title = Wild West Cavey\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|10|7}}\n| ShortSummary = While at a Wild West show in Dodge City, some money disappears from a saddle bag that two bandits who were really actors pretended to steal from a stagecoach that Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels were riding.\n| LineColor = 3abba7\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 22\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 6\n| Title = Cavey's Winter Carnival Caper\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|10|14}}\n| ShortSummary = Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels investigate when their friend, figure skater Karenia Mikovich, disappears.\n| LineColor = 3abba7\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 23\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 7\n| Title = Cavey's Fashion Fiasco\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|10|21}}\n| ShortSummary = At a fashion show, three models disappear.\n| LineColor = 3abba7\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 24\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 8\n| Title = Cavey's Missing Missile Miss-tery\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|10|28}}\n| ShortSummary = Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels decide to investigate when a missile launch they have been watching in the Grand Canyon, where they had previously competed in the Laff-A-Lympics, goes awry.\n| LineColor = 3abba7\n}}\n|}\n\n===Season 3 (1980)===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"width:100%; background:#FFFFFF\"\n|- style=\"color:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#050505; width:20px\"| {{abbr|N\u00ba|Overall episode number}}\n! style=\"background:#050505; width:20px\"| {{abbr|Ep|Episode number by season}}\n! style=\"background:#050505\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#050505; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 25\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 1\n| Title = The Scarifying Seaweed Secret\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1980|3|8}}\n| ShortSummary = Ms. Snowden is supposed to be the heir to a fortune. But she must stay on the island, or her relatives will inherit the fortune. Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels are called in to investigate when the relatives start disappearing thanks to a mysterious sea creature.\n| LineColor = 050505\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 26\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 2\n| Title = The Dummy\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1980|3|15}}\n| ShortSummary = When some jewels are stolen, a ventriloquist whom Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels had been watching the night before is immediately suspected by a policeman.\n| LineColor = 050505\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 27\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 3\n| Title = Cavey and the Volcanic Villain\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1980|3|22}}\n| ShortSummary = In Hawaii, a marriage between two lovers from two families who had been enemies for many years is threatened when a sacred pearl disappears. Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels, who are friends with the bride, investigate.\n| LineColor = 050505\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 28\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 4\n| Title = Prehistoric Panic\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1980|3|29}}\n| ShortSummary = Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels travel back in time to meet Captain Caveman's father, the chief of Cavey's tribe. Cavey soon learns that his father's position is threatened by the Mellog, an evil creature that Captain Caveman's father defeated long ago. Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels investigate when the statue of the Mellog comes to life.\n| LineColor = 050505\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 29\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 5\n| Title = Cavey and the Baffling Buffalo Man\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1980|4|5}}\n| ShortSummary = A Native American park ranger asks Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels for their help in finding his stolen car and the Buffalo Man who stole it.\n| LineColor = 050505\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 30\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 6\n| Title = Dragonhead\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1980|4|12}}\n| ShortSummary = While on the way to a Chinese New Year festival in San Francisco, Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels save a truck driver working for a fortune cookie factory. The CEO, Mr. Chin, has been having problems with his business since a masked criminal named Dragonhead showed up. Captain Caveman finds the truck. They notice that the fortune cookies were stolen but not the fortunes. Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels investigate.\n| LineColor = 050505\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 31\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 7\n| Title = Cavey and the Murky Mississippi Mystery\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1980|4|19}}\n| ShortSummary = Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels go on a cruise on a riverboat on the Mississippi River. While there, some nuclear material disappears in the river. Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels investigate and discover a river creature.\n| LineColor = 050505\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 32\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 8\n| Title = Old Cavey in New York\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1980|4|26}}\n| ShortSummary = In New York City, Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels  witness a blackout. They soon discover that the gold from the International Gold Exchange has been stolen at the same time.\n| LineColor = 050505\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 33\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 9\n| Title = Cavey and the Albino Rhino\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1980|5|3}}\n| ShortSummary = Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels are the first people to see a rare albino rhino at the wildlife park. A little while later, the albino rhino is stolen.\n| LineColor = 050505\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| 